{
  "text": "Samples of total protein (40 μg) were separated by 8% SDS-PAGE and Western blotting was performed. For detection of NPR1 proteins, blots were performed using antibodies raised against NPR1 (a gift from Dr Xinnian Dong, Duke University, NC, USA) at a 1:1000 dilution. Plant MAPKs are highly homologous to mammalian ERK1/2 MAPKs, and anti-phospho-p44/42 antibody can be used to recognize the phosphorylated active MAPK forms in Arabidopsis [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Hence, the endogenous kinase activity of MPK6 after SA treatment was determined using phospho-P44/42 MAPK antibody. For the immunoblot assay, anti-GFP antibody-bound proteins were precipitated by adding protein A-agarose beads (50 μl ml -1 ) to the protein extracts.",
